{
  "texts": [
    "The plus and cross (gauge-invariant) polarizations of the GW waveform are denoted by h + and h ×.",
    "We define the QNMs complex frequencies asσ lm ≡ α lm + iω lm,(2)where Re{σ lm } = α lm ≡ 1/τ lm is the inverse of the damping time, τ lm, while Im{ω n } = ω lm is the oscillation frequency.",
    "A 0,lm and φ 0,lm are the constant amplitudes and phases of the different modes.",
    "Note that in Eq.",
    "( 1) we are neglecting the overtone expansion of each angular mode, since the contribution of overtones in the linear regime (where they can be confidently identified) is negligible compared to the longestlived angular modes [78,86], on which we will focus."
  ]
}